{"lemma":"فَتْرَة","slug":"فَتْرَة","root":"ف.ت.ر","root_slug":"ف-ت-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ت-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"فَتْرَة","root":"فتر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n32909","n32915"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%AA%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"interval, a while, a period of time","examples":[{"text":"بَعْد فَتْرَة","english":"after a while"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"interregnum"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"weariness, relaxedness, languidness, weakness"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n32909","headword_ar":"فتّرهُ","root":"ftr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tafotiyrN","text_ar":"تَفْتِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing, M, O)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to remit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"become allayed"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"still, after vehemence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to become gentle after violence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, O, * K.) ―         -b2-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a worker)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to remit, flag,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"become remiss,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"languid."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ft~r A@ll~`hu AlHar~a","text_ar":"فتّر ا@للّٰهُ الحَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n. as above, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God made the heat to remit after vehemence; to become gentle after violence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made it to remit, abate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flag; to become languid and faint."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ft~r Albaroda","text_ar":"فتّر البَرْدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made the cold to remit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"become allayed."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ft~r AlmaA='a","text_ar":"فتّر المَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made the water to abate in heat so as to become tepid."},{"kind":"text","text":"See 1.] ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ft~r jasadahu","text_ar":"فتّر جَسَدَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(beverage)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heated his body, and made it to become languid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lax in the joints, and weak;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ft~rhu","text_ar":"فتّرهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aftrhu","text_ar":"افترهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"both signify the same, i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it made him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a man's body,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to become languid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lax in the joints, and weak:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or the latter,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(disease, M, K, and intoxication, M)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendered him weak,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"faint:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aftr","text_ar":"افتر"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies [without its objective complement's being expressed]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(beverage)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendered its drinker languid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lax in the joints, and weak;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) or it may have this meaning. (O.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ft~r Als~aHaAbu","text_ar":"فتّر السَّحَابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n. as above, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The cloud continued motionless, and prepared to discharge rain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Abbád, O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rained, and discharged all its water, and left off, and continued motionless:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became motionless:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2331},{"kind":"text","text":"expl. by Hammád Er-Ráwiyeh, in the following verse of Ibn-Mukbil, describing rain, (T,) or a cloud: (TA:)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"taA^am~alo xaliyliY halo taraY Dawo'a baAriqK\n                      \n                     \n                        yamaAnK maratohu riyHu najodK fafat~araA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Look attentively, O my friend; dost thou see the light of a cloud emitting lightning from El-Yemen, from which the wind of Nejd has drawn rain, and which has then continued motionless?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","TA","M","K","As","T"]},{"entry_id":"n32915","headword_ar":"فَتْرَةٌ","root":"ftr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Languor,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remissness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weakness, feebleness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"faintness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an affection like a weakness, feebleness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"faintness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatarN","text_ar":"فَتَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weakness, feebleness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"faintness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajidu fiY nafosiY fatorapF","text_ar":"اَجِدُ فِى نَفْسِى فَتْرَةً"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I experience in myself an affection like a weakness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (T.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An interval of time"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between things:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wtr","text_ar":"وتر"},{"kind":"text","text":"; &c.:) or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between any two prophets,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between two of God's apostles,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"during which there is a cessation of the apostolic function:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cessation of the mission of apostles, and a state of effacement of the signs of their religion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the Kur v. 22. (Msb.)       -A2-  See also what next follows."}],"source_refs":["T","M","K","S","O","TA"]}]}}